<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1591,1978]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1663,1690]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,998,1664,1690]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1042,1347,1664,1691]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="182 - 192" refId="ref27734" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2006) New records of Chloropidae (Diptera) from Southwest Saudi Arabia with some biological information, world-wide geographical distribution and taxonomic features. Saudi Journal of Biological Science 13 (1), 182 - 192." type="journal article" year="2006">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Hawagry, M. S. &amp; Abdel-Dayem, M. S. &amp; El-Sonbati, S. A. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M." pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1499 - 1530" refId="ref28318" refString="El-Hawagry, M. S., Abdel-Dayem, M. S., El-Sonbati, S. A. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M. (2017) A preliminary account of the fly fauna in Garf Raydah, Nature Reserve, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, with new records and biogeographical remarks (Diptera: Insecta). Journal of Natural History, 51 (25 - 26), 1499 - 1530." type="journal article" year="2017">
El-Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[230,287,1700,1726]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[641,758,1700,1726]" name="Cameroon" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Cameroun</collectingCountry>
and further recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1144,1700,1726]" name="Ghana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1302,1700,1726]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1358,1436,1700,1726]" name="Yemen" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[159,331,1736,1762]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="695 - 712" refId="ref29948" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1980) Family Chloropidae. In: Crosskey, R. W. (editor). Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region, pp. 695 - 712. British Museum (Natural History), London. 1437 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">Sabrosky 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Deeming, J. C. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M." box="[344,666,1736,1762]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref28013" refString="Deeming, J. C. &amp; Al-Dhafer, H. M. (2012) Chloropidae from the Arabian Peninsula (Diptera: Cyclorrhapha). Zoology in the Middle East. 58, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="2012">Deeming &amp; Al-Dhafer 2012</bibRefCitation>
). However, there is much material of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1804" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1906" box="[1092,1202,1737,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Oscinis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosa">
<emphasis box="[1092,1202,1737,1762]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">E. rugosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in NMWC from 
<collectingCountry name="Nigeria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[221,297,1772,1798]" name="Ghana" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[308,361,1772,1798]" name="Serbia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Mali</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[416,493,1772,1798]" name="Kenya" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1591,1978]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1808,1834]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was placed in correct generic combination by Becker (2010a) in 
<emphasis box="[1186,1313,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1910" box="[1186,1309,1808,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Epimadiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epimadiza</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
The specimens of this species shows considerable variation in the development of their fore femoral armature. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sabrosky, C. W." pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="821 - 851" refId="ref29681" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1947) A revision of the African genus Epimadiza Becker (Diptera: Chloropidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Ser. 11, 13, 1946, 821 - 851." type="journal article" year="1947">Sabrosky (1947)</bibRefCitation>
cited two rearing records from 
<collectingCountry box="[575,721,1880,1906]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
, being from a cassava stem and “ex 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1828" box="[1121,1254,1880,1906]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Ceroplastes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1121,1254,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ceroplastes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on coffee”. One of us (J.C. Deeming) has reared it from the mines of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="1939" box="[753,863,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Alcidodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[753,863,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Alcidodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[878,1007,1916,1942]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1018,1179,1916,1943]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Curculionidae</taxonomicName>
) in the fibre crop rama (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[161,259,1952,1978]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[161,259,1952,1978]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Hibiscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp.) in Northern 
<collectingCountry box="[451,539,1952,1978]" name="Nigeria" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
: Zaria Province, Jemma’a, Pawadina, Tudun Guadi, 
<date box="[1128,1266,1952,1978]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1966-08-29">29.viii.1966</date>
.
</paragraph>
